\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
IEEE Std 830­1998 IEEE Recommended Practice for Software Requirements Specificat
ions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Document overview
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This document is essentially structured in three parts: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Section 1: Introduction, it gives a description of document and some basic
 information about software.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Section 2: Overall Description, gives general information about the software
 product with more focus about constraints and assumptions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Section 3: Specific Requirements, this part list requirements, typical scenarios
 and use cases.
 To give an easy way to understand all functionality of this software, this
 section is filled with UML diagrams.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Overall Description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Product perspective
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SmartCityAdvisor will be interfaced with Data Control Center's and Traffic
 Control Center's system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moreover our system will be interfaced with his users through a web and
 a mobile application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
User characteristics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The user that we expect to use our applications is a person who want an
 easy way to access to the service we offer.
 The only ability that they need are to be able to use a web browser and
 to download a mobile application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Constraints
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Regulatory policies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SmartCityAdvisor has to comply with all the applicable privacy laws to store
 the sensible user data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Hardware limitation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The only hardware requirements that our product needs to be used by a user
 are a device with a web browser, to access the web application, or smartphone
 running iOS/Android/WinPhone to access the mobile app.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
