\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
User’s Manual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Testing report.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Assumptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assume that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All citizens own a valid email address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Two different citizens can't have the same email address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It's defined, by a specific organization, a threshold of the level of CO2
 admitted in the city of Milan.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If a special event occurs in the center of Milan (e.g., the arrival of some
 VIP, an accident, …), it will be notified at the government of the city.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC is able to limit the traffic that enters in the city center by diverting
 it through paths that avoid the center.
 This is done by controlling the traffic lights using proper actuators.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When TCC receives a request to limit the traffic in the city center by our
 system, it will limit the traffic within 5 minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC is able to write message that will be shown on the display at the main
 entrances of the city.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When the TCC limits the traffic that enters in the city center, it will
 also write a message on the displays to inform the citizens of this.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system knows a list of possible generic health problems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system knows, for each hospital that has established agreements with
 the city of Milan, the specializations available in the hospital, selected
 from the list of possible health problems, and the coordinates of its location.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The health problem of a user who is using our system, is always one which
 is included in the list of possible health problems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All devices (PC and mobile) are provided with a GPS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system is able, given the coordinates of two points, to calculate the
 distance between this points (as the crow flies).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The coordinates of the current position of each user are known through GPS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC is able, given a specific address in Milan, to calculate the coordinate
 of this address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC is able, given the coordinates of two points in Milan, to calculate
 an estimated time to go from the first to the second point by car, considering
 the situation of the traffic at the moment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DCC knows in real-time the length of the queues in the emergency rooms,
 with an associated estimated time to wait, of all the hospitals that has
 established agreements with the city of Milan.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system knows all the parking areas in the center of Milan with their
 coordinates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DCC knows in real-time the availability of all the parking areas in the
 city center.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
There are only three kind of public transports in Milan: underground, tram
 and bus.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system knows the coordinates and the address of all the station of Milan's
 public transports.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DCC knows in real-time the position and current schedule of all public transport
s in the city.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Specific Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
User intarfaces
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Functional requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here the functional requirements identified for each goal:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G1] Citizen should be able to register to the service:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow all citizen to compile the registration form, entering
 name, surname, email and password.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G2] Citizen should be able to login to the service:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system has to provide a login function, with the possibility of recovering
 a forgotten password.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G3] If the level of CO2 in the air is over a specific threshold, access
 to the center should not be allowed to cars, and the citizens should be
 alerted of this (by app and by displays installed at the main entrances
 of the city);
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
When DCC reveals that the level of CO2 in the air of Milan is over the indicated
 threshold, it will advise our system through a specific signal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When the system receives the signal from DCC, it must advise TCC to limit
 the traffic in the city center.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC must confirm to the system that the traffic in the center is going to
 be limited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After TCC has confirmed to the system that the traffic in the center is
 going to be limited, the system must advice all the registered citizens
 of that, through an app notification.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G4] In case of any special situation in the center (e.g., the arrival of
 some VIP, an accident, …), and if the government of Milan think it is necessary
, access to the center should not be allowed to cars and the citizens should
 be alerted of this (by app and by displays installed at the main entrances
 of the city):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
When the government of Milan knows that a special situation is going to
 occur in the center, it will advise our system of that.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After the system has received the information from the government, it must
 advise TCC to limit the traffic in the city center.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TCC must confirm to the system that the traffic in the center is going to
 be limited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After TCC has confirmed to the system that the traffic in the center is
 going to be limited, the system must advice all the registered citizens
 of that, through an app notification.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G5] A registered citizen with a specific health problem, should receive
 suggestions on which hospital to go to receive assistance for his condition
 in the shortest possible time (considering the time to go to the hospital
 and the time to wait in queue):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow a registered citizen to indicate his specific health
 problem and his address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow the user to indicate his position also using GPS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must provide to TCC the coordinates of each hospital that is
 specialized for the indicated health problem, and the coordinates or the
 address where the user is.
 TCC must return to the system an estimated arrival time for each hospital
 that has been communicated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must provide to DCC the list of the hospitals that are specialized
 for the indicated health problem.
 DCC must return to the system an estimated time to wait in the queue for
 each hospital that has been communicated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
After the system has found the hospitals that can assist the user in the
 shortest possible time (considering the time to go to the hospital and
 the time to wait in queue), among those that are specialized for the indicated
 health problem, it must provide to the user information about this hospital.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G6] A registered citizen that want to go to a specific address in the center
 by car, should receive information about the available parking closest
 to the given address (as the crow flies) and the corresponding availability:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow a registered citizen to provide an address in the
 city center where he/she want to go.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow the user to indicate the address also using GPS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the user inserts a textual address, the system must communicate this
 address to TCC.
 TCC must return to the system the coordinates associated to the address.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must communicate to DCC that it needs information about the availabil
ity of all the parking areas in the center, and DCC must provide this informatio
n.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must provide to the user information about the available parking
 area closest to the given address and the corresponding availability.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G7] A registered citizen that want to go to a specific address in Milan,
 using a specific public transport (underground, tram or bus), should receive
 information about the closest (as the crow flies) station where to get
 the selected public transport, the arrival station, the time when the public
 transport will arrive at the starting station, and the estimated time it
 will take to arrive to destination:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow a registered citizen to indicate the starting and
 the arrival address of the trip, and the public transport he/she want to
 use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must allow the user to indicate the addresses also using GPS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the user inserts one or two textual addresses, the system must communicate
 this addresses to TCC.
 TCC must return to the system the coordinates associated to them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must provide to DCC the two stations, of the selected public
 transport, closest to the starting and to the arrival addresses and the
 selected public transport.
 DCC must return to the system the schedule of the first train/tram/bus
 that will pass through the starting station and that is directed toward
 the arrival station.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must provide to the user information about the closest (as the
 crow flies) station where to get the selected public transport, the arrival
 station, the time when the public transport will arrive at the starting
 station, and the estimated time it will take to arrive to destination.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
